The paper deals with the problem of team formation, which involves matching individuals with specific skills and collaboration compatibility to form a team. This problem is commonly studied in the fields of databases (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also proposes a graph pattern matching approach, which is a common technique used in data mining and information retrieval (cs.IR). The dynamic nature of the problem suggests that it may also fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the use of optimization techniques and capacity bounds suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the field of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
